  <preface xml:id="preface">
    <title>Preface</title>
   <p>
  I have designed these notes to get you thinking and working through the material as actively as possible.
</p>
<p>
  Within each section, there is a separate page for each subsection. Each page is intentionally sized so you can complete it in one short sitting, take a break, and then move on to the next subsection page when you are ready!
</p>
<p>
  Here is how you should work through each page:
  <ul>
    <li>Read through the content and work through the examples, revealing hints and solutions as you go.</li>
    <li>Engage with the interactive graphs and checkpoint questions. Don't skip these!</li>
    <li>Once you have worked through the page, watch the video (generally 5-8 minutes long) at the bottom to reinforce the ideas and deepen your understanding.</li>
  </ul>
</p>
<p>
  <alert>Note.</alert> Please read through each page and work through the examples <em>before</em> watching the corresponding lecture video. Learning mathematics requires thinking actively about the material, and watching me explain something on a video is a passive experience. Even if the video makes perfect sense while you're watching, you will retain far less than if you had wrestled with the ideas yourself first.
</p>
  </preface>

</frontmatter>